### Description

When moving between routes DOM nodes are constantly increasing if a component has a `:host-context` css selector with a nested sibling selector (+ or ~), for example:

```
.test-1 {
  :host-context(app-test[data-size="l"]) {
    &:hover + .t-content {
      background: red;
    }
  }
}
```

After forcing the garbage collector, nodes are not deleted. Many detached elements remain: 
<img width="556" alt="Снимок экрана 2024-01-30 в 16 14 20" src="https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/46284632/340f3aed-da84-4f1f-89c1-57a1d6a6deb8">




### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

https://github.com/vladimirpotekhin/min-reproduction

1. npm run start
2. switch between routes several times
3. force the garbage collector
4. domNodes increased, a lot of detached elements

If you remove the sibling selector, then everything becomes ok, the number of DOM nodes returns to the original value after calling the garbage collector 
for example, it's ok:
```
:host-context(app-test[data-size="l"]) {
    &:hover  {
      background: red;
    }
  }
```

